@NODE "DATABASE" "AmigaGuide DATABASE Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

DATABASE <Name>

        This command must be present at the start of all AmigaGuide files
and defines the name of the database.

        It can be set from within AGW using the File Info command.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "TITLE" "AmigaGuide TITLE Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

TITLE <Name>

        This command gives a node a specific title rather than the default
which is the node name.

        It can be set from within AGW using the File Info command.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "NEXT" "AmigaGuide NEXT Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

NEXT <Node>

        This command determines the next node to go to when using the
Browse> command in Amigaguide.

        This information can be set using the Node Info command.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "PREV" "AmigaGuide PREV Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

PREV <Node>

        This command determines the next node to go to when using the
Browse< command in Amigaguide.

        This information can be set using the Node Info command.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "WIDTH" "Width Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

WIDTH <Size>

        This command determines the maximum width of text lines.  Currently
AGW will read/write this command and allow you to set it but does not use
it.

        It can be set from withing AGW using the File Info command.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "HEIGHT" "Height Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

HEIGHT <Size>

        This command determines the maximum number of lines of text to
display in a window.  AGW will read/write this command and allow you to
set it but does not use it.  (I think it is also broken under Wb3.0)

        It can be set from withing AGW using the File Info command.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "WORDWRAP" "WordWrap Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

WORDWRAP

        This command tells AmigaGuide to perform wordwrapping on lines that
are greater than WIDTH.

        It can be set from withing AGW using the File Info command.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "NODE" "AmigaGuide NODE Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

NODE <Name> <Title>

        This marks the beginning of a node.

 <Name> is the node name.
 <Title> is the title to be displayed instead of the Node Name.

        This information can be set using the Node Info command.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ENDNODE" "AmigaGuide ENDNODE command"
@TOC "MAIN"

ENDNODE

        This marks the end of a node.  Text between Node and EndNode is

displayed by AmigaGuide viewers and AGW.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "TOC" "AmigaGuide TOC Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

TOC <Node Name>

        Table of Contents command.  This points to the Node to go to when
the Contents button is hit.

        This field can be set using the Node Info command.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "LINK" "AmigaGuide LINK Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

LINK

        This links a word to a node with optional line numbering.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ALINK" "AmigaGuide ALINK Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

ALINK

        Same as LINK except the node information is shown in a new window.

        This command is currently broken using Wb3.0 AmigaGuide.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "RX" "AmigaGuide RX Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

RX

        Execute the Arexx command given.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "RXS" "AmigaGuide RXS Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

RXS

        Execute the Arexx string given.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "SYSTEM" "AmigaGuide SYSTEM Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

SYSTEM

        Execute the SYSTEM command given.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "QUIT" "AmigaGuide QUIT Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

QUIT

        Quit from AmigaGuide.  Currently broken under Wb3.0?
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Textual" "Textual Commands"
@TOC "MAIN"

Textual Commands

        \@{b}  Turn on Bold
        \@{i}  Turn on Italics
        \@{u}  Turn on Underline
        \@{ub} Turn off Bold
        \@{ui} Turn off Italics
        \@{uu} Turn off Underline

        Currently these commands are read and written but are not settable.
@ENDNODE

